McCormick? I forget his name. I can't remember his 
name. He was an Air Force fighter jockey. I

32:26.193 --> 32:28.616
think... I don't know. It's hard. I've asked 
myself that question. Why did they stay? Tex

32:32.160 --> 32:36.606
Hill is a He's an Orient. He loves the Orient. Like I 
say, he was born and raised over there. As a matter

32:41.987 --> 32:52.837
of fact, Tex still represents certain agencies in 
the Far East today. He spent a lot of time in Taiwan,

32:54.079 --> 32:59.023
Japan, and the Far East. But the other guys, as a 
matter of fact, two out of those five I think were

33:00.365 --> 33:05.850
killed I don't

33:06.100 --> 33:12.827
know. Everybody was just eager to get home now. Oh 
yeah, by far a majority.

33:23.198 --> 33:23.939
Were you sort of sad? Tired, combat weary. I

33:26.762 --> 33:33.930
think really, in my opinion, I'm convinced that 
Texas Amherst's approach to recruit us was by far

33:34.282 --> 33:39.889
the greatest factor for his policy.

33:43.213 --> 33:54.127
And I know had the Air Force, you know it still 
hasn't come around, I think 47 they did something,

33:43.213 --> 33:54.127
the act of 47 on the defense department, that's 
when I got my regular commission, 1947. So I

33:54.187 --> 33:57.551
ultimately achieved that too. But I had the Air 
Force, you know, said, well, look, we'll get an

34:02.834 --> 34:05.858
acronym where we can give. You guys have earned it 
